To have the line number update dynamically when the code changes, you need to modify the `console.log` statement so that it dynamically calculates the line number at runtime instead of hardcoding it at the time of insertion.

### Solution:
You can dynamically calculate the line number using JavaScript's `Error` object or the `stack` property. By creating a custom function to extract the current line number from the stack trace, the logger will always print the correct line number, even if the code changes.

### Dynamic Line Number in JavaScript:
You can use the following approach to dynamically get the current line number:

```javascript
function getCurrentLine() {
    const err = new Error();
    const line = err.stack.split('\n')[2];  // Get the third line of the stack trace (adjust this index if needed)
    const match = line.match(/:(\d+):\d+\)$/);  // Extract the line number from the stack trace
    return match ? match[1] : 'unknown';
}
```

